Ok, the movie 2000mules is out, it is time for everyone to push and politely get into the face of your local State Senators and Representatives and tell them we want bills being composed in their off session interim time on the following Voter Integrity Issues: 


‚Ä¢  We want all our voter rolls cleaned immediately by sending out post cards to everyone and a law saying you just have to keep people on the voter rolls 3 years and 6 months if they haven‚Äôt voted in last election.
‚Ä¢  We want Excuse-Only Mail in Ballots (To compensate we could have No-Excuse In-Person Absentee Ballot for 3 days before election, but no opening of ballots till election day.)
‚Ä¢  No group has real time access to voting progress
‚Ä¢  No opening of any ballots until day of election
‚Ä¢  We want paper ballot hand counted or Dumb Optical Scanners with high speed counters: No flash drives, no Windows, no operating systems, not capable of connecting to the internet, and can only plug into a wall socket.
‚Ä¢  Keep Signature Matching
‚Ä¢  We want voter ID
‚Ä¢  If you get rid of No-excuse Mail in Voting you can easily limit Ballot Drop Boxes to one per county or 100,000 only accessible office hours at county office. (When you go to excuse only, you don‚Äôt need all of these fraudulent drop boxes)
‚Ä¢  Keep all Election Material for 48 Months
‚Ä¢  Any outside independent group can audit the election
‚Ä¢  All Ballots should have an encrypted number: All ballots should have a long encrypted number  like ‚ÄúA759302bzieyh3090303‚Äù that would be in the form of a tear off receipt that only the voter has, and later can go on line to see her/his ballot and therefore all the voters can do their own audit by seeing their actually ballot on line which wouldn‚Äôt of course have any person identifying information on it.
‚Ä¢  Publish Voter Rolls and after elections Ballots on-line
‚Ä¢  No group has access to changing our voter rolls (must submit request)
‚Ä¢  All ballots should also have a sequential number
‚Ä¢  All ballots have watermarks
‚Ä¢  All voters must vote in their own precinct
‚Ä¢  All hand counted votes from all precincts documented on paper and on line locally immediately, then counts given to the county (None of this top down counting, which was done in Georgia, where the local counties didn‚Äôt know their ballot counts until the County told them.)
‚Ä¢  Replace ERIC (Create a conservative ERIC to do the same function in the Red States)
‚Ä¢  All ballot tracking cheating methods banned like Ballottrax and BallotScout that illegally use our tax money and the US Post office for an illegal voter drive and perhaps even TurboVote

States Sue Biden Administration For 'Pressuring And Colluding' With Big Tech To Censor Free Speech

Two Republican-led states have filed a lawsuit against President Joe Biden, White House press secretary Jen Psaki, Dr. Anthony Fauci, and other top administration officials for allegedly pressuring and colluding with social media giants with the aim of censoring and suppressing free speech. 

Missouri Attorney General Eric Schmitt and Louisiana Attorney General Jeff Landry filed the lawsuit in the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Louisiana on April 5, they announced in separate statements on Thursday.

The attorneys claim that Biden and other government officials worked with big tech companies like Meta, Twitter, and YouTube to censor conversation around matters relating to everything from COVID-19 and election integrity to the Hunter Biden laptop story, doing so under the guise of combating ‚Äúmisinformation.‚Äù

Others named in the lawsuit include Surgeon General Vivek Murthy, DHS  Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas, and the executive director of DHS‚Äôs newly established ‚ÄúDisinformation Governance Board,‚Äù Nina Jankowicz. The CDC, the NIAID, HHS Secretary Xavier Becerra, and Director of the Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency Jen Easterly are also listed as defendants.

In announcing the lawsuit on Thursday, attorney Schmitt stressed the importance of freedom of speech which he said is ‚Äúparamount to a healthy society,‚Äù adding that ‚Äúdiscourse, debate, and discussion have been the cornerstone of our country since the Founders codified that right in the Bill of Rights.‚Äù

Schmitt stated that Americans use social media platforms to discuss an array of topics, noting that those topics have more recently been, in light of the global COVID-19 pandemic, conversations regarding whether or not face coverings are effective in preventing the virus from spreading and whether the virus origins came from a lab leak in Wuhan, China.

‚ÄúIn direct contravention to the First Amendment and freedom of speech, the Biden Administration has been engaged in a pernicious campaign to both pressure social media giants to censor and suppress speech and work directly with those platforms to achieve that censorship in a misguided and Orwellian campaign against ‚Äòmisinformation,'‚Äù said Schmitt(MO), referencing George Orwell‚Äôs dystopian novel about a totalitarian state, 1984. The lawsuit filed on Thursday specifically accuses Biden and other government officials of working with big tech companies to remove ‚Äútruthful information related to the lab-leak theory, the efficacy of masks, election integrity, and more,‚Äù Schmitt said.
